Analysing categories on the basis of Time¶

The crimes are very common during the evening hours, though there is a spike in noon, overall, the crime rate is high in the evening till night.¶

District wise analysis of Crimes¶

BayView, Mission has the most crimes in Larceny and Other Offenses. Southern District has an enormous amount of Larceny Crimes while other crimes are negligble as compared to Larceny/Theft. Richmond, Central, Park, Taraval and Northern has a similar pattern.¶

In [7]:
for district in sf_data.PdDistrict.unique():
    df = sf_data.loc[sf_data["PdDistrict"]==district]
    c_counts = df["Category"].value_counts()
    plt.figure(figsize = (15,4)); c_counts.plot.bar(legend=True, title=district); plt.show()

Analysing relationship of crime category with Time and Districts¶

Larceny/Theft is very frequent post 5 in the evening. Other Offenses crime is common during the noon. Non-Criminal ,Assault and Warrant crimes are spread throughout the day evenly. Vehicle theft is frequent in late evening and night .¶

Analysing on the district level, Southern is leading in Larceny, Other offenses, Non-Criminal, Assault, Warrants and Suspicious OCC. Missing Person is very common in Mission distirct as compared to other districts. Drug Narcotic is high in Tenderloin , Southern and Mission.¶

for category in important_categories:
    df = sf_data.loc[sf_data["Category"]==category]
    time_counts = df["Time"].value_counts()
    plt.figure(figsize = (8,4)); time_counts.plot(legend=True, title=category); plt.show()
    dis_counts = df["PdDistrict"].value_counts()
    plt.figure(figsize=(7,4)); dis_counts.plot.bar(legend=True, title=category); plt.show()
